  "prompt_text": "Describe the bittersweet feeling of watching your best friend get married when you're single.",
  "response_text": "Witnessing your best friend's wedding while being single can evoke a complex mix of emotions, often described as bittersweet. On one hand, you're overjoyed for your friend, celebrating their new chapter of life filled with love and commitment. You're genuinely happy for them and excited for their future together.\n\nOn the other hand, it's natural to feel a pang of envy or loneliness. You might find yourself questioning your own love life, wondering when it will be your turn to experience the same joy and companionship. These feelings can be especially intense if you've been single for a while or if you've been hoping to find a partner like the one your friend has found.\n\nHowever, it's important to remember that everyone's timeline is different, and there's no need to rush or compare. Your friend's happiness should be celebrated, and their wedding can serve as a reminder of the kind of love you hope to find. It's a time to cherish the friendship you share and look forward to the future, whether that includes a romantic partner or not.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 8\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 9\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
